   "source": [
    "## Bucketing\n",
    "Using the SimpleReview class again, we will change the summary strategy to \"satisfaction.\" The satisfaction is the star rating converted to a percentage. We will create buckets that represent satisfaction thresholds and output the total employees that fall within these thresholds. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a1655a08",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "43 employees were more than 25% satisfied with their job.\n",
      "38 employees were more than 50% satisfied with their job.\n",
      "28 employees were more than 75% satisfied with their job.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Change summary strategy to satisfaction \n",
    "for r in simple_reviews: \n",
    "    r.set_summary(\"satisfaction\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create list of satisfaction percentages only \n",
    "s_percentages = [r.get_summary() for r in simple_reviews]\n",
    "\n",
    "s_buckets = [25, 50, 75]\n",
    "for x in s_buckets: \n",
    "    total = sum(percentage >= x for percentage in s_percentages)\n",
    "    print(f\"{total} employees were more than {x}% satisfied with their job.\")"
   ]
